give @s written_book[written_book_content={title:"Juggernaut Guide",author:"§9Server",pages:[\
\
[{"text":"Juggernaut\n","bold":true,"color":"dark_red"},{"text":"Game Guide\n\n","bold":true,"color":"gray"},{"text":"One player becomes the ","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"Juggernaut","bold":true,"color":"dark_red"},{"text":" — an unstoppable hunter. Everyone else plays as ","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"Runners","bold":true,"color":"green"},{"text":", working together to survive.","bold":false,"color":"black"}],\
\
[{"text":"The Goal\n","bold":true,"color":"dark_red"},{"text":"Runners ","bold":true,"color":"green"},{"text":"must fill a shared replenishment bar by standing near ","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"Replenishment Stations","bold":true,"color":"gold"},{"text":" scattered across the arena. If the bar is filled, Runners win.\n\nThe ","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"Juggernaut ","bold":true,"color":"dark_red"},{"text":"wins by eliminating every Runner before the bar is completed.","bold":false,"color":"black"}],\
\
[{"text":"Before the Hunt\n","bold":true,"color":"dark_red"},{"text":"When the game starts, the Juggernaut is ","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"locked away","bold":true,"color":"dark_red"},{"text":" for ","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"25 seconds","bold":true,"color":"dark_red"},{"text":". Use this time wisely — spread out across the map and get to a station immediately. Every second counts before the Juggernaut is released.","bold":false,"color":"black"}],\
\
[{"text":"Replenishment Stations\n","bold":true,"color":"gold"},{"text":"Stand within ","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"3 blocks","bold":true,"color":"gold"},{"text":" of a station to begin filling the bar. Multiple Runners can work the same station simultaneously.\n\nProgress ","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"stops completely","bold":true,"color":"dark_red"},{"text":" if the Juggernaut is within ","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"12 blocks","bold":true,"color":"dark_red"},{"text":" of the station.","bold":false,"color":"black"}],\
\
[{"text":"Replenishment Stations\n","bold":true,"color":"gold"},{"text":"Stations emit ","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"totem particles","bold":true,"color":"gold"},{"text":" so you can spot them from a distance.\n\nIf the Juggernaut is nearby, ","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"purple witch particles","bold":true,"color":"dark_purple"},{"text":" appear above the station — a warning to stay away. Rogues can see this warning from up to ","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"24 blocks","bold":true,"color":"dark_purple"},{"text":" away.","bold":false,"color":"black"}],\
\
[{"text":"Completable Stations\n","bold":true,"color":"gold"},{"text":"If this mode is enabled, stations must each be ","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"individually completed","bold":true,"color":"gold"},{"text":" rather than contributing to one shared bar. Out of 8 stations placed, you must complete ","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"5 of them","bold":true,"color":"gold"},{"text":" to win. Completed stations are permanently finished — the Juggernaut cannot undo them.","bold":false,"color":"black"}],\
\
[{"text":"Runner Lives\n","bold":true,"color":"green"},{"text":"Each Runner starts with ","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"juggernauts + 1","bold":true,"color":"green"},{"text":" lives.\n\n","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"1 Juggernaut","bold":true,"color":"dark_red"},{"text":" → 2 lives each\n","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"2 Juggernauts","bold":true,"color":"dark_red"},{"text":" → 3 lives each\n\nLosing all your lives removes you from the game. Survivors kit grants bonus lives.","bold":false,"color":"black"}],\
\
[{"text":"Replenishment Formula\n","bold":true,"color":"gold"},{"text":"The amount of replenishment needed scales with the lobby.\n\n","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"Formula:\n","bold":true,"color":"gold"},{"text":"0.95 × ((base × (total lives − 2) + base) ÷ juggernauts)\n\n","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"Base","bold":true,"color":"gold"},{"text":" is ","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"3500","bold":true,"color":"gold"},{"text":" with completable stations, or ","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"4500","bold":true,"color":"gold"},{"text":" without.","bold":false,"color":"black"}],\
\
[{"text":"Replenishment Formula\n","bold":true,"color":"gold"},{"text":"In practice: more Runners means more total replenishment required. More Juggernauts means each individual Juggernaut requires less replenishment to fill — but there are more hunters.\n\nThe 5% reduction (0.95×) gives Runners a slight edge at larger lobby sizes.","bold":false,"color":"black"}],\
\
[{"text":"Healing\n","bold":true,"color":"aqua"},{"text":"Runners can heal each other. Stand ","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"still and close","bold":true,"color":"aqua"},{"text":" to another Runner (not sprinting or sneaking) to begin healing them.\n\nTo ","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"self-heal","bold":true,"color":"aqua"},{"text":", crouch while stationary. Self-healing is slower than team healing and won't work if you are sprinting.","bold":false,"color":"black"}],\
\
[{"text":"Debuffs\n","bold":true,"color":"red"},{"text":"Hemorrhaged\n","bold":true,"color":"red"},{"text":"You passively lose health over time. Being healed by others does not suppress this.\n\n","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"Mangled\n","bold":true,"color":"red"},{"text":"Healing received from teammates is reversed, damaging you instead. Self-healing is less effective. Both debuffs are applied by certain Juggernaut kits.","bold":false,"color":"black"}],\
\
[{"text":"Chase\n","bold":true,"color":"dark_red"},{"text":"When the Juggernaut is nearby and tracking you, you enter ","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"Chase","bold":true,"color":"dark_red"},{"text":". Several kits and perks react to this state — some Juggernaut kits gain speed stacks the longer a chase continues, while some Runner kits gain bonuses to help them escape.","bold":false,"color":"black"}],\
\
[{"text":"Chase\n","bold":true,"color":"dark_red"},{"text":"Breaking line of sight or creating enough distance ends the chase. Pay attention to your surroundings — staying in chase too long against kits like ","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"Unyielding Wrath","bold":true,"color":"dark_red"},{"text":" makes the Juggernaut progressively faster and harder to escape.","bold":false,"color":"black"}],\
\
[{"text":"Runner Kits\n","bold":true,"color":"green"},{"text":"Each Runner selects a kit before the game begins. Kits define your role and abilities.\n\n","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"Medic","bold":true,"color":"green"},{"text":" — Enhanced healing.\n","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"Scout","bold":true,"color":"green"},{"text":" — Reveals the Juggernaut via line of sight.\n","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"Engineer","bold":true,"color":"green"},{"text":" — Places towers to replenish stations remotely.","bold":false,"color":"black"}],\
\
[{"text":"Runner Kits\n","bold":true,"color":"green"},{"text":"Rogue","bold":true,"color":"green"},{"text":" — Sees the Juggernaut warning particles from farther away.\n","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"Escapist","bold":true,"color":"green"},{"text":" — Built for outrunning the Juggernaut.\n","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"Survivor","bold":true,"color":"green"},{"text":" — Starts with more lives.\n","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"Guide","bold":true,"color":"green"},{"text":" — Supports the team with utility.\n","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"Harbinger","bold":true,"color":"green"},{"text":" — Gains speed bonuses during chase.\n","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"Cloak, Trickster","bold":true,"color":"green"},{"text":" — Deceptive and evasive kits.","bold":false,"color":"black"}],\
\
[{"text":"Juggernaut Kits\n","bold":true,"color":"dark_red"},{"text":"The Juggernaut also selects a kit. Each changes how you hunt.\n\n","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"Classic","bold":true,"color":"dark_red"},{"text":" — Straightforward and reliable.\n","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"Dragon","bold":true,"color":"dark_red"},{"text":" — Breathes fire in a forward cone.\n","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"Predator","bold":true,"color":"dark_red"},{"text":" — Detects Runners through walls when idle.\n","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"Warlock","bold":true,"color":"dark_red"},{"text":" — Controls zones with glyphs and surges.","bold":false,"color":"black"}],\
\
[{"text":"Juggernaut Kits\n","bold":true,"color":"dark_red"},{"text":"Eclipse Stalker","bold":true,"color":"dark_red"},{"text":" — Becomes undetectable.\n","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"Chain Hunter","bold":true,"color":"dark_red"},{"text":" — Tethers Runners with portals.\n","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"Spirit Walker","bold":true,"color":"dark_red"},{"text":" — Phases through blocks.\n","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"Witch Doctor","bold":true,"color":"dark_red"},{"text":" — Applies powerful debuffs.\n","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"Timekeeper","bold":true,"color":"dark_red"},{"text":" — Manipulates movement speed and time.\n","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"Chameleon","bold":true,"color":"dark_red"},{"text":" — Disguises as a Runner to infiltrate.\n","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"Fishmonger, Knight","bold":true,"color":"dark_red"},{"text":" — Unique utility hunters.","bold":false,"color":"black"}],\
\
[{"text":"Perks\n","bold":true,"color":"yellow"},{"text":"If perks are enabled, both sides are assigned ","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"passive bonuses","bold":true,"color":"yellow"},{"text":" at game start. These cannot be chosen — they are given randomly and alter your playstyle.\n\nRunner perks can include faster replenishment, better healing, or improved chase escapes. Juggernaut perks can include bonus damage, zone control, or chase accelerators.","bold":false,"color":"black"}],\
\
[{"text":"Engineer Towers\n","bold":true,"color":"green"},{"text":"Engineers can place towers near Replenishment Stations. Towers auto-replenish nearby stations without a Runner needing to stand there.\n\nIf a tower is placed ","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"away from a station","bold":true,"color":"green"},{"text":", it replenishes at full speed. If placed ","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"beside a station","bold":true,"color":"green"},{"text":", it works at 1/3 speed.","bold":false,"color":"black"}],\
\
[{"text":"Engineer Towers\n","bold":true,"color":"green"},{"text":"Towers can be ","bold":false,"color":"black"},{"text":"dispelled","bold":true,"color":"dark_red"},{"text":" by the Juggernaut standing near them long enough. A bell sound plays when a tower is destroyed. Engineers have separate cooldowns for revealing towers, replenishment towers, and turrets.","bold":false,"color":"black"}],\
\
[{"text":"Tips for Runners\n","bold":true,"color":"green"},{"text":"- Split up early and hit multiple stations at once.\n- Watch for purple particles before approaching a station.\n- Don't self-heal in the open — crouch carefully.\n- Stick with a teammate when possible for mutual healing.\n- If Mangled, avoid being healed — it will hurt you.","bold":false,"color":"black"}],\
\
[{"text":"Tips for Juggernaut\n","bold":true,"color":"dark_red"},{"text":"- Patrol between stations rather than chasing one Runner endlessly.\n- Staying near a station denies all progress there.\n- Extended chases power up kits like Unyielding Wrath.\n- Use your kit abilities to split groups or cut off escapes.\n- Prioritize low-life Runners to reduce the replenishment target.","bold":false,"color":"black"}]\
\
]}]